12
00:01:49,900 --> 00:01:53,466
- [Renfroe] It's been said that you can never go home again.

13
00:01:53,500 --> 00:01:56,900
I know that as a young boy growing up on a farm

14
00:01:56,933 --> 00:02:00,633
in rural Louisiana was the greatest experience of my life.

15
00:02:01,933 --> 00:02:04,100
So I decided to make one more trip

16
00:02:04,133 --> 00:02:07,466
to see the old home place and remember the smell

17
00:02:07,500 --> 00:02:09,933
of Mama's wood stove cooking cornbread and peas.

18
00:02:11,100 --> 00:02:13,133
- How long has it been since you been here?

19
00:02:16,566 --> 00:02:17,800
- Quite awhile.

20
00:02:21,766 --> 00:02:24,266
(light music)

21
00:02:30,233 --> 00:02:32,433
- [Renfroe] The days were long, but we didn't care

22
00:02:32,466 --> 00:02:35,433
because of the fun we had as kids,

23
00:02:35,466 --> 00:02:39,033
fishing and making kites out of old newspapers.

24
00:02:39,066 --> 00:02:41,466
Sometime, D.J., my older brother,

25
00:02:41,500 --> 00:02:43,766
would let me actually try to fly one of them.

26
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:47,833
(harmonica music)

27
00:02:54,333 --> 00:02:57,966
Nutty, a young neighbor boy living with his grandparents

28
00:02:58,000 --> 00:03:00,900
was the best kite flier I think I ever saw.

29
00:03:02,266 --> 00:03:06,200
He and D.J. were always trying to scare me with stories

30
00:03:06,233 --> 00:03:09,300
about an old panther at night.

31
00:03:09,333 --> 00:03:11,033
(Renfroe laughs)

32
00:03:11,066 --> 00:03:12,933
"Screaming like a woman," they'd say.

33
00:03:16,133 --> 00:03:18,300
I remember a special year in my life

34
00:03:18,333 --> 00:03:19,866
that changed me forever.

35
00:03:21,233 --> 00:03:24,333
To this day, I think about that time

36
00:03:24,366 --> 00:03:28,933
when I would sit around and daydream of snow on Christmas.

37
00:03:30,866 --> 00:03:34,166
Clara Mae made a new angel for our Christmas tree that year

38
00:03:34,200 --> 00:03:37,266
and I got to keep the old one.

39
00:03:38,700 --> 00:03:41,466
I took it and nailed it up on the front of the barn

40
00:03:42,600 --> 00:03:45,366
and every time I walked by her,

41
00:03:45,400 --> 00:03:48,133
she seemed to be watching my every move,

42
00:03:48,166 --> 00:03:49,933
regardless of where I was standing.

43
00:03:52,033 --> 00:03:54,200
Now even as a grown man,

44
00:03:54,233 --> 00:03:58,433
I still believe in angels and miracles.

45
00:04:02,100 --> 00:04:03,833
It seems like only yesterday

46
00:04:03,866 --> 00:04:06,533
when Papa was ringing that old dinner bell

47
00:04:06,566 --> 00:04:08,766
and we'd all come running from the fields.

48
00:04:10,166 --> 00:04:12,766
(upbeat music)

49
00:04:19,233 --> 00:04:21,833
(upbeat music)

50
00:04:28,300 --> 00:04:31,000
(upbeat music)

51
00:04:31,033 --> 00:04:34,266
- Renfroe, you boys need to wash up for supper.

52
00:04:34,300 --> 00:04:37,233
- Nutty always gets the fly the kite.

53
00:04:37,266 --> 00:04:41,233
- Well, there's far more practicing to do, Renfroe.

54
00:04:41,266 --> 00:04:43,233
I'll teach you how to do it tomorrow.

55
00:04:43,266 --> 00:04:45,066
- Thanks, you better.

56
00:04:46,500 --> 00:04:48,333
Have to knock you out.

57
00:04:50,966 --> 00:04:53,533
(upbeat music)

58
00:05:01,500 --> 00:05:02,733
- Renfroe, did you wash up?

59
00:05:02,766 --> 00:05:03,833
- Yes, ma'am.

60
00:05:07,700 --> 00:05:09,200
- How about we say the blessing.

61
00:05:09,233 --> 00:05:11,566
Our heavenly Father, we are grateful for your blessings

62
00:05:11,600 --> 00:05:13,666
and for watching over us through these hard times

63
00:05:13,700 --> 00:05:15,066
across our land.

64
00:05:15,100 --> 00:05:16,733
The bounties that you have given us,

65
00:05:16,766 --> 00:05:20,233
we now partake of, we are ever so thankful, amen.

66
00:05:23,933 --> 00:05:27,400
D.J., D.J., in the morning, I want you and Renfroe

67
00:05:27,433 --> 00:05:29,233
to make sure you go out there and stack it.

68
00:05:29,266 --> 00:05:30,766
We may have a real bad winter.

69
00:05:31,833 --> 00:05:32,733
- [D.J.] Yes, sir.

70
00:05:35,566 --> 00:05:40,000
- Papa, are you expecting it to be real cold this winter?

71
00:05:40,033 --> 00:05:41,433
- It may be, Renfroe.

72
00:05:41,466 --> 00:05:43,766
And we wanna make sure we're ready for it if it is.

73
00:05:46,133 --> 00:05:47,933
- Well, maybe it will snow.

74
00:05:49,533 --> 00:05:52,166
(upbeat music)

75
00:05:53,733 --> 00:05:55,666
- [Papa] It just might.

76
00:05:59,466 --> 00:06:01,400
- D.J., did you hear what Papa said last night

77
00:06:01,433 --> 00:06:02,433
at the supper table?

78
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:05,366
- I heard him say you need to help me cut

79
00:06:05,400 --> 00:06:06,500
and stack this wood.

80
00:06:07,500 --> 00:06:08,900
- He also said it may snow.

81
00:06:10,200 --> 00:06:11,633
- I figure it'll be hot enough today

82
00:06:11,666 --> 00:06:13,700
when me and Nutty go down to the fishing hole

83
00:06:13,733 --> 00:06:16,233
while you stack this wood and daydream about snow.

84
00:06:18,166 --> 00:06:20,966
- D.J., Renfroe!

85
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:26,033
D.J., fishing, the fish aren't gonna wait forever.

86
00:06:29,500 --> 00:06:30,900
Whew!

87
00:06:30,933 --> 00:06:33,433
Now, why haven't y'all finished with this wood yet?

88
00:06:33,466 --> 00:06:35,533
- Well, if you get over here and help us stack it,

89
00:06:35,566 --> 00:06:37,600
we can get finished a lot quicker.

90
00:06:37,633 --> 00:06:39,666
- [Nutty] Okay, y'all, we gotta hurry up

91
00:06:39,700 --> 00:06:41,966
and get to the fishing hole pretty soon.

92
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:44,333
Those bass are just gonna up and leave us.

93
00:06:44,366 --> 00:06:47,133
- Well, Renfroe's over there daydreaming about snow.

94
00:06:47,166 --> 00:06:48,766
- Y'all remember last Christmas

95
00:06:49,866 --> 00:06:51,266
when the third wiseman tripped and fell

96
00:06:51,300 --> 00:06:53,900
at the at the altar during Christmas program?

97
00:06:55,300 --> 00:06:57,300
- Why'd he trip?

98
00:06:57,333 --> 00:07:01,833
- On account of his trick knee, it started acting up

99
00:07:01,866 --> 00:07:05,100
and when he was kneeling down at baby Jesus' feet,

100
00:07:06,933 --> 00:07:08,566
the candle flew right out of his hand

101
00:07:08,600 --> 00:07:10,766
right on baby Jesus' manger,

102
00:07:10,800 --> 00:07:14,266
but of course, it really wasn't the real baby Jesus.

103
00:07:15,133 --> 00:07:16,933
(cast scream)

104
00:07:16,966 --> 00:07:20,166
- Fire, the baby!

105
00:07:20,200 --> 00:07:22,500
(cast scream)

106
00:07:22,533 --> 00:07:26,133
♪ Joy to the world ♪

107
00:07:26,166 --> 00:07:28,133
(congregation laughs)

108
00:07:28,166 --> 00:07:32,033
♪ Joy to the world, the Lord is come ♪

109
00:07:32,066 --> 00:07:36,633
♪ Let earth receive her king ♪

110
00:07:36,666 --> 00:07:39,233
♪ Let every heart ♪

111
00:07:39,266 --> 00:07:42,166
♪ Prepare him room ♪

112
00:07:42,200 --> 00:07:44,866
- It wasn't the real baby Jesus.

113
00:07:46,066 --> 00:07:49,166
- Renfroe, Nutty's not stupid.

114
00:07:49,200 --> 00:07:52,500
He knows it wasn't the real baby Jesus.

115
00:07:52,533 --> 00:07:53,566
- I didn't know.

116
00:07:53,600 --> 00:07:55,266
I didn't know what kind

117
00:07:55,300 --> 00:07:57,266
of Bible training Nutty might have had.

118
00:07:58,500 --> 00:08:00,566
- I sure would've liked to seen that.

119
00:08:02,100 --> 00:08:03,266
My grandparents saw it

120
00:08:03,300 --> 00:08:05,133
and said the whole thing was real funny.

121
00:08:07,200 --> 00:08:10,333
My parents would've liked to have seen it, too.

122
00:08:10,366 --> 00:08:12,733
(light music)

123
00:08:12,766 --> 00:08:13,600
Oh well.

124
00:08:15,766 --> 00:08:18,266
(light music)

125
00:08:24,966 --> 00:08:27,466
(light music)

126
00:08:34,133 --> 00:08:36,633
(light music)

127
00:08:43,166 --> 00:08:45,666
(light music)

128
00:08:47,200 --> 00:08:48,800
- Come on now, let's get out of here.

129
00:08:48,833 --> 00:08:50,233
- You mean it? - Yeah, let's go.

130
00:08:50,266 --> 00:08:51,100
- Yes!

131
00:08:52,300 --> 00:08:53,566
Think them bass will bite?

132
00:08:53,600 --> 00:08:54,400
- Oh yeah, come on.

133
00:08:54,433 --> 00:08:55,233
- Come on, let's go.

134
00:08:55,266 --> 00:08:56,100
Let's go!

135
00:08:57,200 --> 00:08:59,766
(upbeat music)

136
00:09:01,866 --> 00:09:05,533
We'll get a fish and stay away from town.

137
00:09:05,566 --> 00:09:06,633
Yeehaw, whoo!

138
00:09:11,066 --> 00:09:13,666
(upbeat music)

139
00:09:15,100 --> 00:09:15,933
- Come on!

140
00:09:17,966 --> 00:09:20,433
Last one there is a dead fish.

141
00:09:20,466 --> 00:09:23,766
(upbeat music)

142
00:09:23,800 --> 00:09:25,200
- D.J. and you gotta be more careful

143
00:09:25,233 --> 00:09:28,000
when Nutty's around talking about Christmas here

144
00:09:28,033 --> 00:09:29,866
with our parents and all.

145
00:09:29,900 --> 00:09:31,700
Heard what he said about his parents.

146
00:09:31,733 --> 00:09:36,000
It's gonna take him a long time getting over losing them.

147
00:09:36,033 --> 00:09:37,600
- I just forgot.

148
00:09:37,633 --> 00:09:39,600
We didn't mean any harm to Nutty.

149
00:09:39,633 --> 00:09:41,366
He's around here so much,

150
00:09:41,400 --> 00:09:43,533
I kind of feel like he's part of the family.

151
00:09:43,566 --> 00:09:44,900
Don't you, Clara?

152
00:09:44,933 --> 00:09:47,900
- Keep in mind what I said.

153
00:09:47,933 --> 00:09:49,500
Holidays are a hard time of the year

154
00:09:49,533 --> 00:09:51,633
for people who've lost folks.

155
00:09:51,666 --> 00:09:53,666
Talk about, mm, fishing.

156
00:09:56,733 --> 00:09:58,933
- I know it's a little bit too soon to be talking

157
00:09:58,966 --> 00:10:03,133
about Christmas and all, but I believe I'll be getting lots

158
00:10:03,166 --> 00:10:05,333
of presents this year.

159
00:10:05,366 --> 00:10:07,500
- Getting presents isn't the chief joy

160
00:10:07,533 --> 00:10:09,166
of Christmas, Renfroe.

161
00:10:09,200 --> 00:10:12,100
- Then what is one of the chief joys?

162
00:10:12,133 --> 00:10:16,200
- Well, gift giving is a special pleasure.

163
00:10:16,233 --> 00:10:20,300
It is more blessed to give than to receive.

164
00:10:20,333 --> 00:10:22,566
- [Renfroe] I believe I like getting presents best,

165
00:10:22,600 --> 00:10:25,066
no matter what's more blessed.

166
00:10:25,100 --> 00:10:28,466
- I've noticed you've become a little selfish here lately.

167
00:10:28,500 --> 00:10:30,466
- [Renfroe] Is that trough a manger?

168
00:10:30,500 --> 00:10:31,933
- Yes, it is.

169
00:10:31,966 --> 00:10:35,566
And you know, Renfroe, whenever I hear the Christmas story,

170
00:10:35,600 --> 00:10:39,733
I can see it all happen right here in this very stable.

171
00:10:40,933 --> 00:10:42,166
Selfishness is something

172
00:10:42,200 --> 00:10:44,333
you can make up your mind to overcome.

173
00:10:45,766 --> 00:10:48,233
(light music)

174
00:10:59,200 --> 00:11:01,866
(birds chirping)

175
00:11:06,300 --> 00:11:09,133
(Renfroe hollers)

176
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:16,333
- Renfroe, will you stop it?

177
00:11:20,166 --> 00:11:21,866
(Renfroe hollers)

178
00:11:21,900 --> 00:11:22,733
- Renfroe!

179
00:11:23,766 --> 00:11:25,300
Got Indians after you?

180
00:11:28,633 --> 00:11:33,633
(Renfroe shouts) (upbeat music)

181
00:11:41,366 --> 00:11:42,833
- [D.J.] What now?

182
00:11:44,066 --> 00:11:46,633
(upbeat music)

183
00:11:53,500 --> 00:11:56,033
(upbeat music)

184
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:01,266
- Hey, look at me, D.J..

185
00:12:01,300 --> 00:12:03,233
I'm a champion bull rider.

186
00:12:03,266 --> 00:12:04,100
Woo hoo!

187
00:12:05,566 --> 00:12:07,133
Coming up, come on.

188
00:12:08,333 --> 00:12:09,666
Hurry up and go.

189
00:12:11,600 --> 00:12:15,633
Come on, Renfroe, my grandma's faster than you are.

190
00:12:15,666 --> 00:12:18,233
(upbeat music)

191
00:12:22,433 --> 00:12:24,466
- Y'all wait up.

192
00:12:24,500 --> 00:12:27,100
(upbeat music)

193
00:12:33,400 --> 00:12:35,966
(upbeat music)

194
00:12:42,733 --> 00:12:45,300
(upbeat music)

195
00:12:52,566 --> 00:12:55,433
(upbeat music)

196
00:12:55,466 --> 00:12:57,533
- Another panther track.

197
00:12:57,566 --> 00:12:59,033
- A panther track?

198
00:13:00,866 --> 00:13:02,100
- Are you sure?

199
00:13:03,233 --> 00:13:05,933
- Yep, we heard it again the other night.

200
00:13:05,966 --> 00:13:07,300
- [D.J.] We did.

201
00:13:08,466 --> 00:13:11,200
(dramatic music)

202
00:13:17,766 --> 00:13:20,500
(dramatic music)

203
00:13:26,966 --> 00:13:29,733
(dramatic music)

204
00:13:36,633 --> 00:13:39,633
- Are y'all sure that's a panther track?

205
00:13:39,666 --> 00:13:42,833
- [D.J.] Yep, sure is a panther track.

206
00:13:48,833 --> 00:13:51,000
- I think I wanna go home.

207
00:14:00,333 --> 00:14:02,200
- What are you drawing, Renfroe?

208
00:14:02,233 --> 00:14:06,566
- An angel, I'm making a few changes on our old one.

209
00:14:12,466 --> 00:14:15,133
(rooster crows)

210
00:14:25,066 --> 00:14:27,466
(bell rings)

211
00:14:37,233 --> 00:14:39,766
- Renfroe Ty Madison, get out of that cupboard.

212
00:14:39,800 --> 00:14:42,000
It's time to go to school, you're gonna be late.

213
00:14:42,033 --> 00:14:43,700
- But Mama, I'm hungry.

214
00:14:43,733 --> 00:14:45,366
- Come put your hat and coat on.

215
00:14:52,400 --> 00:14:53,233
There.

216
00:14:55,600 --> 00:14:56,500
That's right.

217
00:14:56,533 --> 00:14:57,366
Hey, what's that drawing?

218
00:14:57,400 --> 00:14:58,933
- It's my angel.

219
00:14:58,966 --> 00:15:00,266
- Well, it's not Christmas yet,

220
00:15:00,300 --> 00:15:02,266
but it is supposed to get cold today.

221
00:15:03,166 --> 00:15:04,000
Bye. - Bye.

222
00:15:08,700 --> 00:15:11,266
(upbeat music)

223
00:15:22,100 --> 00:15:23,700
(bell rings)

224
00:15:23,733 --> 00:15:26,466
(children cheer)

225
00:15:28,000 --> 00:15:29,300
- Bye, Ms. Watson.

226
00:15:29,333 --> 00:15:30,833
- Bye, Ms. Watson.

227
00:15:38,533 --> 00:15:41,133
(upbeat music)

228
00:15:42,066 --> 00:15:43,866
- Go on, go home.

229
00:15:43,900 --> 00:15:46,000
- Be quiet, you big bully.

230
00:15:46,033 --> 00:15:47,633
- You kids go home.

231
00:15:48,833 --> 00:15:51,433
(upbeat music)

232
00:15:57,000 --> 00:15:58,233
- How was your day?

233
00:15:58,266 --> 00:15:59,200
- Pretty good.

234
00:15:59,233 --> 00:16:00,666
- What's that?

235
00:16:00,700 --> 00:16:01,766
- A secret.

236
00:16:01,800 --> 00:16:02,600
- What you got?

237
00:16:02,633 --> 00:16:03,433
- It's a secret.

238
00:16:03,466 --> 00:16:04,666
- Tell me.

239
00:16:04,700 --> 00:16:06,100
- You can't keep a secret, Renfroe.

240
00:16:07,333 --> 00:16:08,300
- Yes, I can.

241
00:16:08,333 --> 00:16:10,033
- No, you can't.

242
00:16:10,066 --> 00:16:11,000
- Yes, I can.

243
00:16:11,033 --> 00:16:13,200
- I know better than that.

244
00:16:15,866 --> 00:16:17,933
- [Renfroe] Give it back!

245
00:16:19,333 --> 00:16:20,166
D.J.!

246
00:16:22,100 --> 00:16:23,566
Buford, that's my hat.

247
00:16:27,433 --> 00:16:30,033
- [Clara Mae] Nutty, no, no, no.

248
00:16:30,966 --> 00:16:32,366
Renfroe, you best clear.

249
00:16:32,400 --> 00:16:33,966
- D.J.'s coming, Buford.

250
00:16:34,000 --> 00:16:38,066
He's gonna get you.

251
00:16:38,100 --> 00:16:40,200
- Let this be a warning to you.

252
00:16:40,233 --> 00:16:41,700
Don't mess with my little brother.

253
00:16:41,733 --> 00:16:43,500
- Yeah, Madison, you're scaring me.

254
00:16:47,633 --> 00:16:49,300
- Come on, let's go.

255
00:16:52,166 --> 00:16:54,766
(upbeat music)

256
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:02,833
- I can't wait, one more week.

257
00:17:02,866 --> 00:17:04,033
- One week till what?

258
00:17:05,833 --> 00:17:08,000
- Well, I overheard Ms. Watson say we were getting off

259
00:17:08,033 --> 00:17:08,933
for Christmas in a week.

260
00:17:08,966 --> 00:17:10,366
Didn't you hear her say that?

261
00:17:10,400 --> 00:17:11,600
- Yeah, I heard her.

262
00:17:11,633 --> 00:17:13,800
Next time that bully Buford Reynolds picks

263
00:17:13,833 --> 00:17:17,066
on another little one, I'm gonna clean his plow.

264
00:17:17,100 --> 00:17:19,333
- But D.J., he's too big for you.

265
00:17:20,666 --> 00:17:23,400
(upbeat music)

266
00:17:23,433 --> 00:17:26,866
- But that Buford does need a good old fashioned whooping.

267
00:17:26,900 --> 00:17:29,633
(Renfroe laughs)

