00:35:25,900 --> 00:35:28,533
- Let's see here how this is going to add up.

537
00:35:28,566 --> 00:35:31,300
Wow, I may wind up owing you money.

538
00:35:31,333 --> 00:35:34,066
- Well, that'll be fine.

539
00:35:34,100 --> 00:35:35,900
- How's everything out at the place?

540
00:35:35,933 --> 00:35:37,500
- We're doing fine.

541
00:35:39,066 --> 00:35:41,133
- Let's see here.

542
00:35:41,166 --> 00:35:44,466
A good year for hams, so I'm glad.

543
00:35:44,500 --> 00:35:47,833
Boy, well, I owe you 75 cents this year.

544
00:35:48,933 --> 00:35:50,166
- How about that.

545
00:35:50,200 --> 00:35:53,066
- How about a nice knife for Renfroe?

546
00:35:53,100 --> 00:35:55,133
Got some good bargains.

547
00:35:55,166 --> 00:35:56,633
- Young Renfroe's mother would sell me

548
00:35:56,666 --> 00:35:59,033
at a bargain if she found out that I paid 75 cents

549
00:35:59,066 --> 00:36:01,766
for a knife on a boy who already has one.

550
00:36:01,800 --> 00:36:04,600
- But one of the blades is broken.

551
00:36:04,633 --> 00:36:06,100
- You know, but however,

552
00:36:06,133 --> 00:36:08,066
you didn't exactly go out of the way to tell her.

553
00:36:08,100 --> 00:36:10,433
- [Papa] If 75 cents would buy two knives,

554
00:36:10,466 --> 00:36:12,000
I might consider it.

555
00:36:12,033 --> 00:36:14,333
- Well, I've got some real bargains in here all the way

556
00:36:14,366 --> 00:36:16,466
from 10 cents to a dollar.

557
00:36:21,300 --> 00:36:24,100
- Renfroe, do you think you could trade out the 75 cents

558
00:36:24,133 --> 00:36:26,033
on a knife for yourself and one for D.J.

559
00:36:26,066 --> 00:36:28,166
while I go down to the dry goods store?

560
00:36:28,200 --> 00:36:30,300
- Okay, sir.

561
00:36:30,333 --> 00:36:32,400
- Are you a pretty good trader, Renfroe?

562
00:36:33,266 --> 00:36:34,300
- Oh yes, sir.

563
00:36:35,933 --> 00:36:38,500
- Okay, let me show you something in here.

564
00:36:38,533 --> 00:36:41,433
Oh, I've got some really good bargains in here.

565
00:36:42,600 --> 00:36:44,466
Look at this knife right here, Renfroe.

566
00:36:44,500 --> 00:36:46,333
This thing is just 35 cent.

567
00:36:49,633 --> 00:36:52,600
You could get two of those, even have a nickel left

568
00:36:52,633 --> 00:36:54,966
to buy some candy with.

569
00:36:55,000 --> 00:36:57,500
What do you think about that?

570
00:36:57,533 --> 00:37:00,100
(light music)

571
00:37:07,200 --> 00:37:08,266
Okay, you have to be careful.

572
00:37:08,300 --> 00:37:11,200
Don't cut your finger with that.

573
00:37:11,233 --> 00:37:13,000
Isn't that a nice one?

574
00:37:13,033 --> 00:37:14,533
You like that one?

575
00:37:15,633 --> 00:37:17,400
And look at this, Renfroe.

576
00:37:18,733 --> 00:37:20,300
It's only 25 cents.

577
00:37:21,700 --> 00:37:25,833
You could get this one and that one for 75 cent.

578
00:37:25,866 --> 00:37:27,266
It'd be an even trade.

579
00:37:28,400 --> 00:37:32,066
- Well, I'll take these two. - Okay.

580
00:37:32,100 --> 00:37:35,233
Okay, and wrap this one in a paper.

581
00:37:35,266 --> 00:37:37,133
- Okay, and are you gonna put this one in your pocket

582
00:37:37,166 --> 00:37:38,366
or you want me to wrap it?

583
00:37:38,400 --> 00:37:41,900
- Uh-huh, I'll put it in my pocket.

584
00:37:41,933 --> 00:37:43,266
- All right.

585
00:37:43,300 --> 00:37:45,066
Are you anxious for Christmas?

586
00:37:45,100 --> 00:37:46,400
- Oh, yes, sir.

587
00:37:46,433 --> 00:37:49,366
- [Peabody] What else you might have gotten?

588
00:37:49,400 --> 00:37:51,400
- I don't know.

589
00:37:51,433 --> 00:37:55,400
- [Peabody] Well, I hope you have a very special Christmas.

590
00:37:55,433 --> 00:37:56,966
- I hope you do, too, sir.

591
00:37:57,000 --> 00:37:58,333
- Merry Christmas to you.

592
00:37:58,366 --> 00:37:59,833
- Merry Christmas to you, too, sir.

593
00:37:59,866 --> 00:38:01,533
- All right.

594
00:38:01,566 --> 00:38:04,066
(light music)

595
00:38:05,966 --> 00:38:07,233
Bye. - Bye, sir.

596
00:38:09,033 --> 00:38:11,533
