601
00:38:51,300 --> 00:38:53,533
- Why, hello there, Renfroe.

602
00:38:53,566 --> 00:38:54,900
- Hi, Mrs. Gibbons!

603
00:38:54,933 --> 00:38:55,966
- I need to talk to you.

604
00:38:56,000 --> 00:38:57,633
Can we sit for awhile?

605
00:38:57,666 --> 00:38:59,600
- [Renfroe] Yes, ma'am.

606
00:39:00,766 --> 00:39:02,100
- Christmas is a week from tomorrow

607
00:39:02,133 --> 00:39:03,833
and I'm wondering if I can count on you

608
00:39:03,866 --> 00:39:05,133
to be on the program?

609
00:39:06,266 --> 00:39:09,433
- Oh, yes, ma'am, you could call on me.

610
00:39:09,466 --> 00:39:12,100
- Well, after the pageant, we're going to be having a party

611
00:39:12,133 --> 00:39:14,500
with refreshments and entertainment.

612
00:39:14,533 --> 00:39:17,066
I thought you could do one of your imitations.

613
00:39:17,100 --> 00:39:18,833
I heard you're good at them.

614
00:39:18,866 --> 00:39:19,700
- I am.

615
00:39:20,900 --> 00:39:23,166
Yes, ma'am, I'll try to make you up one.

616
00:39:23,200 --> 00:39:25,600
- Good, and would you tell Clara Mae and D.J.

617
00:39:25,633 --> 00:39:27,966
that I'd like them to be on the program also.

618
00:39:28,000 --> 00:39:29,133
But I'll talk to them more about it

619
00:39:29,166 --> 00:39:30,633
at Sunday school tomorrow.

620
00:39:30,666 --> 00:39:32,366
- Yes, ma'am, and thank you for asking me.

621
00:39:32,400 --> 00:39:33,733
- Sure, bye-bye.

622
00:39:39,600 --> 00:39:41,100
- Merry Christmas.

623
00:39:43,300 --> 00:39:44,800
(light music)

624
00:39:44,833 --> 00:39:47,366
- Here, it's for you.

625
00:39:47,400 --> 00:39:50,033
Pa don't want you to tell Mom on account

626
00:39:50,066 --> 00:39:54,933
of ladies don't always understand boys and knives.

627
00:39:54,966 --> 00:39:56,333
- Pa get you one?

628
00:39:56,366 --> 00:39:58,133
- Well, a little one.

629
00:39:59,166 --> 00:40:01,500
- Come on, let's get a ride.

630
00:40:02,633 --> 00:40:05,133
(light music)

631
00:40:11,566 --> 00:40:14,066
(light music)

632
00:40:23,933 --> 00:40:28,033
("Hark, the Herald Angels Sing")

633
00:40:34,600 --> 00:40:38,700
("Hark, the Herald Angels Sing")

634
00:40:46,266 --> 00:40:47,566
- Isn't that right, Renfroe?

635
00:40:47,600 --> 00:40:48,800
- What's right?

636
00:40:48,833 --> 00:40:52,866
- You having a crush on Ms. Gibbons and all.

637
00:40:52,900 --> 00:40:54,166
- It ain't so!

638
00:40:54,200 --> 00:40:55,433
I ain't gonna tell you the message

639
00:40:55,466 --> 00:40:57,766
that she told me to give y'all.

640
00:40:57,800 --> 00:40:59,133
- What message?

641
00:40:59,166 --> 00:41:00,866
You're making it up.

642
00:41:00,900 --> 00:41:03,100
- What did she say to you, Renfroe?

643
00:41:03,133 --> 00:41:04,400
Tell us, does she want us to be

644
00:41:04,433 --> 00:41:07,833
in the Christmas program this year?

645
00:41:07,866 --> 00:41:10,533
- Tell us, Mama's boy, before I put the hurt on you.

646
00:41:10,566 --> 00:41:13,300
- Okay, okay, she does, she does!

647
00:41:13,333 --> 00:41:16,600
She wants y'all to meet her at Sunday school

648
00:41:16,633 --> 00:41:20,300
and I guess she'll give you the parts there.

649
00:41:21,833 --> 00:41:25,966
("Hark, the Herald Angels Sing")

650
00:41:29,566 --> 00:41:32,833
She asked me to do an imitation

651
00:41:32,866 --> 00:41:35,933
that will please young and old alike.

652
00:41:37,566 --> 00:41:40,433
- She'll probably want me to be a wiseman.

653
00:41:40,466 --> 00:41:42,233
She'll probably want me to play my viola

654
00:41:42,266 --> 00:41:43,533
which she usually ask me again.

655
00:41:43,566 --> 00:41:45,100
- Oh, come on, D.J..

656
00:41:45,133 --> 00:41:47,000
Everybody likes that viola.

657
00:41:47,033 --> 00:41:51,566
It's a true gift and you really should share it.

658
00:41:51,600 --> 00:41:54,400
- Renfroe, you haven't done imitations in two years.

659
00:41:54,433 --> 00:41:56,533
You still can't do them.

660
00:41:56,566 --> 00:41:58,600
- There is a brain, D.J..

661
00:42:04,300 --> 00:42:08,400
("Hark, the Herald Angels Sing")

662
00:42:15,033 --> 00:42:19,100
("Hark, the Herald Angels Sing")

663
00:42:26,933 --> 00:42:29,500
(upbeat music)

664
00:42:30,900 --> 00:42:33,833
And all of the sudden, crazy Nathan started to get up

665
00:42:33,866 --> 00:42:35,900
from the front pew.

666
00:42:35,933 --> 00:42:38,600
- Well, it is not good Christmas spirit

667
00:42:38,633 --> 00:42:41,000
to refer to poor Nathan as crazy.

668
00:42:41,033 --> 00:42:42,633
I know other boys and girls call him that,

669
00:42:42,666 --> 00:42:45,633
but I don't wanna ever hear y'all call him that.

670
00:42:45,666 --> 00:42:47,733
- It's uncharitable, Renfroe.

671
00:42:47,766 --> 00:42:50,000
- Why, 'cause he's your sweetheart?

672
00:42:50,033 --> 00:42:51,733
- And that's unkind, too.

673
00:42:51,766 --> 00:42:55,500
Making any kind of joke about Nathan is not nice.

674
00:42:55,533 --> 00:42:58,733
- I was glad to hear the Claytons won't have to be moving.

675
00:42:58,766 --> 00:43:00,133
- [Mama] How's that?

676
00:43:00,166 --> 00:43:02,033
- I overheard him in the bank the other day.

677
00:43:02,066 --> 00:43:05,066
Seems that President Roosevelt has opened up the WPA.

678
00:43:05,100 --> 00:43:08,066
Mr. Clayton took a road job at 35 cents an hour.

679
00:43:08,100 --> 00:43:09,733
He starts after Christmas.

680
00:43:09,766 --> 00:43:12,866
- Well, I'm happy for them, especially the children.

681
00:43:12,900 --> 00:43:15,600
Clara Mae, why don't you help me fix a food basket.

682
00:43:15,633 --> 00:43:18,166
We'll have plenty and they've had such hard times.

683
00:43:18,200 --> 00:43:19,966
- Yes, ma'am, I'd like that.

684
00:43:20,000 --> 00:43:21,466
- I'm glad they ain't moving.

685
00:43:21,500 --> 00:43:23,200
I like the girls.

686
00:43:23,233 --> 00:43:26,533
- Now, Renfroe, about that imitation,

687
00:43:26,566 --> 00:43:28,666
I don't think anybody wants to be reminded

688
00:43:28,700 --> 00:43:30,966
of what happened at last year's pageant.

689
00:43:31,000 --> 00:43:34,066
So why don't you see if you can't think of another one.

690
00:43:34,100 --> 00:43:34,933
- Yes'm.

691
00:43:36,033 --> 00:43:37,833
- Maybe it's uncharitable of me,

692
00:43:37,866 --> 00:43:40,200
but I don't think anyone could sound as terrible

693
00:43:40,233 --> 00:43:41,700
as Mr. Franz Martin.

694
00:43:41,733 --> 00:43:43,233
(Clara Mae laughs) (D.J. laughs)

695
00:43:43,266 --> 00:43:45,033
- Thanks, Papa, me neither.

696
00:43:46,666 --> 00:43:49,200
- I understand they're sending Nathan to a special school

697
00:43:49,233 --> 00:43:51,333
for handicapped children up in the mountains

698
00:43:51,366 --> 00:43:52,800
after the holidays.

699
00:43:52,833 --> 00:43:55,900
I hear the civic club is paying for him to go there.

700
00:43:55,933 --> 00:43:58,366
Now, Renfroe, about your imitation...

701
00:44:00,000 --> 00:44:02,633
(birds chirping)

702
00:44:07,966 --> 00:44:10,800
(thunder rumbles)

703
00:44:16,566 --> 00:44:17,966
- [D.J.] Taking all day.

704
00:44:18,000 --> 00:44:19,466
- All right, get back, get back.

705
00:44:19,500 --> 00:44:21,466
Nobody's gonna get a present until I give them to you.

706
00:44:23,333 --> 00:44:24,800
- All right. - Hurry up!

707
00:44:24,833 --> 00:44:25,933
- First one for you, Clara Mae.

708
00:44:25,966 --> 00:44:27,566
- Come on, Mama.

709
00:44:27,600 --> 00:44:28,633
You're the slowest person--

710
00:44:28,666 --> 00:44:30,666
- I hope that's what you want.

711
00:44:30,700 --> 00:44:32,133
- Grandma Ebony.

712
00:44:32,166 --> 00:44:34,800
- I should've put switches in those packages, go.

713
00:44:34,833 --> 00:44:36,433
Go ahead, open it, let's see it.

714
00:44:36,466 --> 00:44:38,300
- First, Laura, then Grandma Ebony.

715
00:44:38,333 --> 00:44:39,533
- Look! - Oh wow.

716
00:44:39,566 --> 00:44:42,200
- [Mama] Patience, it's a virtue.

717
00:44:42,233 --> 00:44:43,633
- [Renfroe] Gimme!

718
00:44:43,666 --> 00:44:44,866
- [Mama] Do you like them?

719
00:44:44,900 --> 00:44:46,800
- Oh wow, thank you. - [Renfroe] Mama!

720
00:44:46,833 --> 00:44:48,033
- [D.J.] Those are nice, Clara.

721
00:44:48,066 --> 00:44:50,100
- I figured for out in the garden.

722
00:44:50,133 --> 00:44:52,166
One for you, D.J..

723
00:44:52,200 --> 00:44:53,766
- [Papa] What is it, D.J., charcoal?

724
00:44:53,800 --> 00:44:56,033
- I don't know, it's got a knot in it.

725
00:44:56,066 --> 00:44:57,700
- Here's one for you, Renfroe.

726
00:44:57,733 --> 00:44:58,633
- Ooh, I got a biggie.

727
00:44:58,666 --> 00:44:59,433
- [Papa] Wow, look at that one.

728
00:44:59,466 --> 00:45:00,233
What have you got there?

729
00:45:00,266 --> 00:45:01,533
- I wonder what that is.

730
00:45:01,566 --> 00:45:03,100
- Looks like a wiener to me.

731
00:45:03,133 --> 00:45:04,433
- [Mama] He knows how to fly.

732
00:45:04,466 --> 00:45:05,700
- Oh, I got a yo-yo.

733
00:45:05,733 --> 00:45:07,166
- [Papa] A yo-yo.

734
00:45:08,233 --> 00:45:10,366
- [Mama] There you go.

735
00:45:10,400 --> 00:45:11,800
Whoa.

736
00:45:11,833 --> 00:45:13,700
- [Papa] Renfroe, you been wanting a lasso for a long time.

737
00:45:13,733 --> 00:45:14,733
Now you have one.

738
00:45:14,766 --> 00:45:16,200
- Papa, here's one for you.

739
00:45:16,233 --> 00:45:17,433
- Oh wow, looka here.

740
00:45:17,466 --> 00:45:18,366
- Ooh, that pretty paper.

741
00:45:18,400 --> 00:45:20,933
- What do you think it is, guys?

742
00:45:20,966 --> 00:45:21,833
- [D.J.] I don't know.

743
00:45:21,866 --> 00:45:23,633
- A velvet dress.

744
00:45:23,666 --> 00:45:25,433
It's a velvet dress.

745
00:45:25,466 --> 00:45:27,566
- What I'd do with a dress, Renfroe?

746
00:45:27,600 --> 00:45:28,966
- Thanks, Santa!

747
00:45:29,000 --> 00:45:31,333
- Have you ever played with a yo-yo before?

748
00:45:31,366 --> 00:45:32,933
You look like you know how to do it.

749
00:45:32,966 --> 00:45:34,566
- [Renfroe] Don't worry about a yo-yo.

750
00:45:34,600 --> 00:45:36,100
- A napkin.

751
00:45:36,133 --> 00:45:39,266
- No, these are handkerchiefs for Christmas for church days.

752
00:45:39,300 --> 00:45:40,466
- And this one's for me.

753
00:45:40,500 --> 00:45:41,666
- [Papa] Oh, great, Mama.

754
00:45:41,700 --> 00:45:43,000
- [Clara Mae] Those are nice.

755
00:45:43,033 --> 00:45:45,966
- Look, it's my favorite potpourri.

756
00:45:47,366 --> 00:45:48,166
- [D.J.] Okay, Mom.

757
00:45:48,200 --> 00:45:49,800
- They fit like a glove.

758
00:45:49,833 --> 00:45:51,600
- Fit just like a glove.

759
00:45:51,633 --> 00:45:53,833
- Oh look, it's beautiful!

760
00:45:54,733 --> 00:45:55,933
- [Renfroe] What is it?

761
00:45:55,966 --> 00:45:58,466
- Well, it's a comb, a brush and a mirror set.

762
00:45:58,500 --> 00:45:59,800
- [Renfroe] What is that?

763
00:45:59,833 --> 00:46:00,800
- [Mama] Look how lovely.

764
00:46:00,833 --> 00:46:02,366
(Renfroe shouts)

765
00:46:02,400 --> 00:46:03,900
Thank you so much.

766
00:46:04,900 --> 00:46:06,066
Oh, I love it.

767
00:46:06,100 --> 00:46:08,033
- [Papa] You're right, a yo-yo.

768
00:46:08,066 --> 00:46:11,000
("O Christmas Tree")

769
00:46:11,033 --> 00:46:13,266
- [Mama] Oh, there's another one for Renfroe.

770
00:46:13,300 --> 00:46:15,333
- Gimme, gimme, gimme, gimme!

771
00:46:15,366 --> 00:46:16,866
- [D.J.] How many does Renfroe get?

772
00:46:16,900 --> 00:46:20,266
- [Papa] What do you think it could be?

773
00:46:20,300 --> 00:46:21,400
- [D.J.] What is it, Renfroe?

774
00:46:21,433 --> 00:46:22,233
- [Papa] What is it, son?

775
00:46:22,266 --> 00:46:23,433
- I don't know.

776
00:46:23,466 --> 00:46:25,466
Stop asking me that many questions.

777
00:46:25,500 --> 00:46:28,300
- [D.J.] It sounds like it's a...

778
00:46:29,366 --> 00:46:30,966
- [Clara Mae] Look!

779
00:46:32,300 --> 00:46:35,166
- This is the best present I've ever had.

780
00:46:35,200 --> 00:46:36,533
- You're welcome, Renfroe, merry Christmas.

781
00:46:36,566 --> 00:46:37,766
- Thank you, Mommy.

782
00:46:37,800 --> 00:46:41,800
- You are welcome, thank you, merry Christmas.

