00:48:08,800 --> 00:48:10,566
- Hey there, son.

795
00:48:10,600 --> 00:48:12,100
I was hoping someone would come along

796
00:48:12,133 --> 00:48:13,766
and give me the correct time.

797
00:48:13,800 --> 00:48:17,900
- Well, if you don't mind waiting four more minutes,

798
00:48:17,933 --> 00:48:19,366
it'd be 10.

799
00:48:19,400 --> 00:48:20,566
- I don't mind waiting.

800
00:48:20,600 --> 00:48:22,933
I have lots of time, it's Christmas.

801
00:48:24,366 --> 00:48:27,000
- Mama, can I go to the Claytons?

802
00:48:27,033 --> 00:48:29,400
- That'll be fine, son, but remember

803
00:48:29,433 --> 00:48:32,333
that an earache could keep you out of the Christmas program.

804
00:48:32,366 --> 00:48:34,600
So put your hat on and make sure your flaps are down

805
00:48:34,633 --> 00:48:37,266
over your ears, button your coat up good.

806
00:48:37,300 --> 00:48:38,200
- Yes'm.

807
00:48:38,233 --> 00:48:39,100
- Don't be gone too long.

808
00:48:43,000 --> 00:48:45,566
(upbeat music)

809
00:48:47,366 --> 00:48:48,933
- Renfroe's coming.

810
00:48:50,033 --> 00:48:52,000
Hey, guys, Renfroe's coming.

811
00:48:52,033 --> 00:48:53,100
- [Mary Martha] I figured he'd be around here

812
00:48:53,133 --> 00:48:54,866
sometime this morning.

813
00:48:54,900 --> 00:48:56,066
- [Lucy] I bet you did not.

814
00:48:57,433 --> 00:48:59,833
- [Mary Martha] Hey, Renfroe, did Santa come see you?

815
00:48:59,866 --> 00:49:01,100
- Sure did.

816
00:49:01,133 --> 00:49:02,166
- Merry Christmas, Renfroe.

817
00:49:02,200 --> 00:49:03,700
- Merry Christmas to you, too.

818
00:49:07,500 --> 00:49:09,000
What'd he bring you?

819
00:49:09,033 --> 00:49:13,133
- A diamond ring and a velvet dress, plus a few other things

820
00:49:13,166 --> 00:49:14,800
that aren't any of your business.

821
00:49:16,233 --> 00:49:21,033
- Oh man, Martha, how come you make up them lies like that?

822
00:49:21,066 --> 00:49:23,666
She got the same as the rest of us.

823
00:49:23,700 --> 00:49:24,666
That's what she got.

824
00:49:24,700 --> 00:49:26,033
- You don't know.

825
00:49:26,066 --> 00:49:26,966
I might have hidden my presents

826
00:49:27,000 --> 00:49:28,966
before you got up this morning.

827
00:49:29,000 --> 00:49:33,833
- Hey, Renfroe, I got an orange, an apple and some candy.

828
00:49:33,866 --> 00:49:35,200
- Well, that wasn't hardly worth

829
00:49:35,233 --> 00:49:37,533
hanging up a stocking for, was it?

830
00:49:37,566 --> 00:49:38,733
- Oh, yes it was.

831
00:49:38,766 --> 00:49:40,266
The candy and apple were good

832
00:49:40,300 --> 00:49:42,733
and I'm saving the orange for tomorrow.

833
00:49:42,766 --> 00:49:46,166
- Pretty nice of Santa to leave you that jump rope, Renfroe.

834
00:49:46,200 --> 00:49:48,533
- That's not a jump rope, that's a lasso.

835
00:49:48,566 --> 00:49:51,633
Besides that, I got a yo-yo and this.

836
00:49:56,733 --> 00:49:59,066
- My word, that's beautiful!

837
00:50:00,966 --> 00:50:03,066
- Reckon the same Santa Claus

838
00:50:03,100 --> 00:50:06,166
that came to your house came to ours?

839
00:50:07,333 --> 00:50:09,700
- Well, let's play jump rope with your lasso.

840
00:50:11,633 --> 00:50:14,233
(upbeat music)

841
00:50:21,166 --> 00:50:23,766
(upbeat music)

842
00:50:30,800 --> 00:50:31,933
- Girls, it's supper time.

843
00:50:31,966 --> 00:50:34,066
Y'all come on in.

844
00:50:34,100 --> 00:50:35,333
- [Girls] Okay.

845
00:50:35,366 --> 00:50:38,166
- Fried chicken, you can even serve upside down.

846
00:50:38,200 --> 00:50:41,500
- With chops and with chestnuts and a mama and a dad.

847
00:50:41,533 --> 00:50:43,666
- We're not having chicken tonight.

848
00:50:43,700 --> 00:50:48,400
Instead, we're having fried steak, pork chops, ice cream

849
00:50:48,433 --> 00:50:49,300
and chocolate pie.

850
00:50:50,433 --> 00:50:52,200
- [Clarrie] Mary Martha, there you go again

851
00:50:52,233 --> 00:50:54,433
making up them whopping tales.

852
00:50:54,466 --> 00:50:57,666
- If you go, we won't have a rope to play with.

853
00:50:59,233 --> 00:51:01,700
(upbeat music)

854
00:51:06,733 --> 00:51:08,500
- [Roosevelt] Now, first of all,

855
00:51:08,533 --> 00:51:11,066
let me assert my firm belief

856
00:51:12,466 --> 00:51:17,066
that the only thing we have to fear is fear itself.

857
00:51:22,500 --> 00:51:23,333
- Amen.

858
00:51:26,333 --> 00:51:29,333
(upbeat music)

859
00:51:29,366 --> 00:51:34,366
- [Clara Mae] Pass that salt.

860
00:51:35,766 --> 00:51:39,333
- Mrs. Madison, you have outdone yourself this time.

861
00:51:39,366 --> 00:51:43,533
("We Wish You A Merry Christmas")

862
00:51:50,533 --> 00:51:54,666
("We Wish You A Merry Christmas")

863
00:52:00,500 --> 00:52:05,466
- Papa, do you mind if I do my imitation at the table?

864
00:52:06,200 --> 00:52:08,033
- [Papa] Go ahead, son.

865
00:52:08,066 --> 00:52:11,200
- Now, I ain't gonna tell y'all what this is.

866
00:52:11,233 --> 00:52:13,766
So y'all are just gonna have to guess.

867
00:52:13,800 --> 00:52:15,333
- This ought to be interesting.

868
00:52:15,366 --> 00:52:18,066
(D.J. laughs)

869
00:52:18,100 --> 00:52:20,866
- Imitation by Renfroe Ty Madison.

870
00:52:22,700 --> 00:52:27,700
(Renfroe clucks) (Renfroe neighs)

871
00:52:29,933 --> 00:52:32,533
(Renfroe taps)

872
00:52:33,433 --> 00:52:36,100
(Renfroe blows)

873
00:52:39,500 --> 00:52:42,866
That's it, now one of you have to try to guess.

874
00:52:42,900 --> 00:52:44,166
- I don't have to guess.

875
00:52:44,200 --> 00:52:45,933
It's a herd of wild horses.

876
00:52:45,966 --> 00:52:48,933
- Horses don't rattle, D.J..

877
00:52:48,966 --> 00:52:51,966
- Well, it could be a skeleton chasing him

878
00:52:52,000 --> 00:52:54,166
and his old jawbones were rattling.

879
00:52:54,200 --> 00:52:57,000
(Renfroe laughs) - No, D.J., that's not it.

880
00:52:57,033 --> 00:52:58,300
- I'll bet I can get it.

881
00:52:58,333 --> 00:52:59,166
- [Renfroe] Bet you can't.

882
00:52:59,200 --> 00:53:00,633
- I'll bet I can.

883
00:53:00,666 --> 00:53:03,466
The neighing and galloping wasn't done by horses,

884
00:53:03,500 --> 00:53:05,233
mules or donkeys.

885
00:53:05,266 --> 00:53:06,533
It was by reindeer.

886
00:53:08,200 --> 00:53:11,133
- No, no, no, not that either.

887
00:53:12,100 --> 00:53:13,766
Guess I'll just have to explain.

888
00:53:16,666 --> 00:53:19,233
All right, now,

889
00:53:21,600 --> 00:53:25,733
snow and snow falling on a tin roof.

890
00:53:27,066 --> 00:53:30,666
That's why you were so close, Papa, about that rain.

891
00:53:30,700 --> 00:53:33,033
- [D.J.] Sound like a hail storm to me.

892
00:53:33,066 --> 00:53:35,900
- Renfroe, dear, snow doesn't make any noise.

893
00:53:35,933 --> 00:53:38,966
It falls without a sound, but then you wouldn't know that

894
00:53:39,000 --> 00:53:40,566
because you've never seen snow.

895
00:53:43,100 --> 00:53:44,566
- I wish it would snow.

896
00:53:46,200 --> 00:53:47,966
I hear it makes real good ice cream.

897
00:53:48,000 --> 00:53:49,200
- Oh, it does.

898
00:53:49,233 --> 00:53:50,433
It's delicious.

899
00:53:50,466 --> 00:53:52,000
It's the best I've ever had.

900
00:53:52,033 --> 00:53:55,900
- This Christmas, it'll be one to remember.

901
00:53:55,933 --> 00:53:58,000
It will snow, snow, snow.

902
00:54:03,833 --> 00:54:06,333
(light music)

903
00:54:13,700 --> 00:54:16,200
(light music)

904
00:54:18,966 --> 00:54:22,733
Get down, Belle, you know this tree.

905
00:54:22,766 --> 00:54:23,933
Aw, it's okay.

906
00:54:26,100 --> 00:54:30,333
Well, merry Christmas to you, too.

907
00:54:30,366 --> 00:54:32,433
Hey, D.J., Renfroe, come on, guys.

908
00:54:32,466 --> 00:54:34,066
Hurry up!

909
00:54:34,100 --> 00:54:36,266
- Hey, Nutty, what'd you get for Christmas?

910
00:54:37,766 --> 00:54:40,266
(Nutty sighs)

911
00:54:42,533 --> 00:54:44,433
- [Nutty] Nothing yet.

912
00:54:44,466 --> 00:54:45,300
- Nothing?

913
00:54:47,433 --> 00:54:49,500
- Why, Christmas is almost over.

914
00:54:49,533 --> 00:54:50,966
- Now, I know that, Renfroe,

915
00:54:52,800 --> 00:54:55,000
but my grandparents ordered me some new clothes

916
00:54:55,033 --> 00:54:56,733
and they just haven't come in yet.

917
00:54:58,733 --> 00:55:01,466
(light music)

918
00:55:01,500 --> 00:55:04,000
- Well, didn't they get you anything to play with?

919
00:55:05,433 --> 00:55:08,100
- Well, they weren't feeling into going in town

920
00:55:08,133 --> 00:55:09,133
as they had planned.

921
00:55:10,366 --> 00:55:12,166
(light music)

922
00:55:12,200 --> 00:55:13,733
Oh, but that's okay.

923
00:55:13,766 --> 00:55:15,066
At least they're feeling better now.

924
00:55:15,100 --> 00:55:16,633
And that's okay, that's much better

925
00:55:16,666 --> 00:55:19,633
than any gift I could ever get.

926
00:55:19,666 --> 00:55:21,400
- Too bad they didn't feel better yesterday

927
00:55:21,433 --> 00:55:24,400
when all the stores were open.

928
00:55:24,433 --> 00:55:26,933
(light music)

929
00:55:27,800 --> 00:55:29,233
- Hey, that's pretty nice!

930
00:55:29,266 --> 00:55:31,133
But I guess you'll be expecting me to believe

931
00:55:31,166 --> 00:55:33,000
that it keeps time.

932
00:55:33,033 --> 00:55:35,033
- Believe it and see it keeping time.

933
00:55:35,066 --> 00:55:38,666
That little bitty hand there ticks off every single second.

934
00:55:41,033 --> 00:55:44,100
- Hey, D.J., y'all are as good as old man Bruce Watson.

935
00:55:44,133 --> 00:55:45,300
- Better, I'd say.

936
00:55:45,333 --> 00:55:48,200
- Well, I need some practice.

937
00:55:48,233 --> 00:55:51,800
- Hey, Renfroe, why don't you let me have a try at that?

938
00:55:55,300 --> 00:55:57,933
You know, I'm willing to bet money

939
00:55:57,966 --> 00:55:59,866
that that's what my grandparents were gonna get me

940
00:55:59,900 --> 00:56:01,166
if they'd gone into town.

941
00:56:01,200 --> 00:56:04,733
I need practice on a really nice yo-yo.

942
00:56:08,633 --> 00:56:11,400
- Look, y'all, I can yo-yo from the top step.

943
00:56:12,533 --> 00:56:14,266
- Why can't you yo-yo from right there?

944
00:56:14,300 --> 00:56:16,133
- 'Cause the string's too long and he won't cut it.

945
00:56:16,166 --> 00:56:18,600
He thinks he's gonna grow into it.

946
00:56:22,366 --> 00:56:23,500
- Hey, it's nice, Renfroe,

947
00:56:23,533 --> 00:56:25,400
but why can't you yo-yo from right there?

948
00:56:25,433 --> 00:56:28,200
Renfroe, why don't you let me have a try at that yo-yo?

949
00:56:29,466 --> 00:56:30,633
- Here, you have a try.

950
00:56:33,200 --> 00:56:34,033
- Thanks.

951
00:56:35,166 --> 00:56:37,733
Now, how in Sam Hill do you work this thing?

952
00:56:40,100 --> 00:56:41,333
Now, how do I work this thing?

953
00:56:41,366 --> 00:56:45,200
- Well, first you make a special knot in the end.

954
00:56:45,233 --> 00:56:47,733
(light music)

955
00:56:50,600 --> 00:56:51,433
Here you go.

956
00:56:51,466 --> 00:56:52,300
- Thanks.

957
00:56:53,500 --> 00:56:56,000
(light music)

958
00:56:59,300 --> 00:57:01,266
- Now, D.J., it's worse than before.

959
00:57:01,300 --> 00:57:02,400
Change it back.

960
00:57:05,033 --> 00:57:06,900
Great, D.J..

961
00:57:06,933 --> 00:57:08,100
Fix it back, D.J..

962
00:57:08,133 --> 00:57:09,466
Now it's all messed up.

963
00:57:09,500 --> 00:57:10,700
It's worser than before.

964
00:57:10,733 --> 00:57:11,966
Fix it back.

965
00:57:12,000 --> 00:57:13,200
- Only if you let Nutty play with it

966
00:57:13,233 --> 00:57:14,466
for a little bit longer.

967
00:57:14,500 --> 00:57:16,233
- He can play with it for a little bit longer

968
00:57:16,266 --> 00:57:17,300
and that's all.

969
00:57:19,600 --> 00:57:21,400
- [Nutty] How do you do it, just up and down?

970
00:57:21,433 --> 00:57:22,233
- Yeah.

971
00:57:22,266 --> 00:57:23,533
- [Nutty] Okay.

972
00:57:27,033 --> 00:57:29,733
- John Brownit, if those ain't snow clouds,

973
00:57:29,766 --> 00:57:31,400
I don't know what is.

974
00:57:32,866 --> 00:57:35,766
- Renfroe, you wouldn't know a snow cloud from a rain cloud.

975
00:57:37,233 --> 00:57:39,933
- Uh, look like rain clouds to me, too, Renfroe.

976
00:57:43,066 --> 00:57:45,466
(thunder rumbles)

977
00:57:45,500 --> 00:57:48,700
Yep, that's rain clouds all right.

978
00:57:48,733 --> 00:57:52,533
- Clara Mae, don't those look like snow clouds to you?

979
00:57:52,566 --> 00:57:54,100
- You're daydreaming, Renfroe.

980
00:57:54,133 --> 00:57:54,966
Come on.

981
00:57:56,766 --> 00:57:59,033
- Oh no, not milking again.

982
00:58:00,233 --> 00:58:03,766
Nutty, return my yo-yo, I need it.

983
00:58:03,800 --> 00:58:04,966
- Here you go.

984
00:58:08,933 --> 00:58:11,066
Can I take a turn?

985
00:58:11,100 --> 00:58:15,500
- Maybe I should at least let Nutty have it till tomorrow

986
00:58:15,533 --> 00:58:18,033
or at least till after Christmas clothes, don't you think?

987
00:58:18,066 --> 00:58:20,400
- You should've let him keep it, period, Renfroe.

988
00:58:20,433 --> 00:58:21,966
That's what you should've done.

989
00:58:22,000 --> 00:58:23,600
You could've let Nutty have it.

990
00:58:23,633 --> 00:58:24,633
Hey, get up.

991
00:58:25,900 --> 00:58:27,100
- But why should I?

992
00:58:27,133 --> 00:58:28,800
Nutty's grandparents have more money

993
00:58:28,833 --> 00:58:30,700
than most folks hereabout.

994
00:58:30,733 --> 00:58:33,066
Nutty's grandpa is retired from the railroad

995
00:58:33,100 --> 00:58:35,900
and probably can run and buy him all sorts of fancy things.

996
00:58:35,933 --> 00:58:37,966
- But he doesn't have anything now.

997
00:58:38,000 --> 00:58:40,066
And now it's Christmas.

998
00:58:40,100 --> 00:58:42,733
You don't have to have all the things you got today.

999
00:58:42,766 --> 00:58:45,266
You could've let Nutty have some little something.

1000
00:58:46,733 --> 00:58:50,066
You got a watch, you got a lasso and you got a yo-yo.

1001
00:58:51,133 --> 00:58:52,466
Anything you would've given Nutty

1002
00:58:52,500 --> 00:58:54,366
would've made him very happy.

1003
00:58:54,400 --> 00:58:57,733
- Course if I were a rich boy and got two or three bicycles

1004
00:58:57,766 --> 00:58:59,833
and a whole wagon load of other stuff,

1005
00:58:59,866 --> 00:59:02,500
I'd probably give him at least one of my presents.

1006
00:59:03,600 --> 00:59:05,700
- Ought to be ashamed of yourself.

1007
00:59:05,733 --> 00:59:06,866
- I hadn't heard you sing

1008
00:59:06,900 --> 00:59:08,366
O Come, All Ye Faithful this year.

1009
00:59:08,400 --> 00:59:11,266
- That's right, Renfroe, just change the subject.

1010
00:59:11,300 --> 00:59:13,800
I'll be singing it tonight at the Christmas program,

1011
00:59:13,833 --> 00:59:15,800
but you, young man, in the meantime,

1012
00:59:15,833 --> 00:59:18,966
you need to be thinking a lot about sharing.

